.40 S&W, Chromed Barrel, steel construction, DA/SA and a VERY cool "tri-action" system.

title: For Sale:  Glock 19 with BlackHawk! Serpa II - $600 if you want all the extras I have
postcontent:
I can sell this Glock without the Crimson Trace and 31 round magazine for $450. That is a sweet deal for this condition of the pistol. I am pretty sure I know what it is worth considering my buddy got one in same exact condition for $500. Glocks can shoot thousands of rounds with minimal wear and tear so this is a great piece considering I have not shot it very much. I have almost $800 in this picture. 

I have a Glock 19 that was purchased on December 21, 2010. I bought it because my best friend had the same pistol and we wanted to have complete interchangeability between the handguns with magazines, holsters, and accessories we may buy. We shoot guns every Saturday and I would clean it every week even if I did not shoot it that week. This gun is my baby and has not had much ammo through it. I carried it more than I shot it and it has minimal holster wear on the slide. It comes with a Scherer 31 round magazine with a +2 baseplate. The magazine doesn't feed hollowpoints very well but works good with Full Metal Jacket rounds. I kept it loaded up with 28 rounds and in my car for if I had a really bad day. Comes with a BRAND SPANKIN' new Crimson Trace laser that I just installed on it. The laser is a wonder in itself! You can shoot from the most twisted uncomfortable positions (for example, under a car or leaning around a wall with only a small amount of yourself exposed) and be accurate. The laser is currently sighted in to be accurate from 5 steps away to as far as you can shoot and see your target. The laser also helps in dry fire practice because you can actually see if the laser moves when you pull the trigger and dry fire. It has helped me become a much better shooter. If you have never owned a handgun with a Crimson Trace you need to see what you are missing. They are incredible!
It also comes with a BlackHawk! Serpa level II holster in Gun Metal Gray. The holster really accents the Glock Tenifer finish and stands out above the crowd. I have had more than one person say "Dude, that is a sick Glock you have there!"
I have the gun-lock that comes with it, the cleaning rod and bore brush (has not been used!) the fired brass from the factory, and all the cool pamphlets that Glock gives you when you buy one of their pistols.
So why am I selling such a great pistol? I really have my heart set on buying an AR-15 rifle. I am also interested in S&W M&P sub-compact handguns. .40 S&W is possible but 9mm would be the best! I have my eye on the new Smith&Wesson M&P15 as well.

Send me a text or give me a call if you are serious about buying because I always have my phone on me and I can answer further questions about it or arrange a meet. If you are just semi interested send me an email and I'll get back with you asap.
